      passage: `The following text is adapted from Kenneth Grahame’s 1908 novel <i>The Wind in the Willows</i>. The Mole is dazed after briefly meeting a stranger while traveling with a friend.<br><br>The Mole stood still a moment, held in thought. As one wakened suddenly from a beautiful dream, who struggles to recall it, and can re-capture nothing but a dim sense of the beauty of it, the beauty! Till that, too, fades away in its turn.`,
